CatDescriptText: John Crenshaw, steel mill worker, 4738 Sylvan Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 8, 1959, pg. B1 with question: "Do you believe the John James Racket Squad is driving the numbers racket out of Pittsburgh?" answer reads: "I believe that the raiding squad is helping. Some places have been closed down."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of John Crenshaw wearing striped short sleeved shirt with light colored buttons, and light colored cap, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
